     8	---
     9	
    10	# ADR-0.7.0 — Vector binary quantization (Pack 1 + Pack 2)
    11	
    12	**Status:** draft, HITL-required.
    13	
    14	This ADR records the data-encoding decision that closes AC-013 (and
    15	collaterally AC-019) within the proposed 80 / 300 ms envelope in
    16	0.7.0. It is paired with — and feeds into — the numeric lock-flip
    17	that will be made post-Pack-2 against
    18	`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md`. That ADR
    19	remains the budget owner; this ADR commits the architectural shape
    20	that makes those budgets reachable.
    21	
    22	## 1. Problem
    23	
    24	Canonical-CI measurement on 2026-05-27 under the locked
    25	W4.1-stacked-O1 (`L-Y1+L-Y2+L-B5+L-B4+L-D1-pcache2-O1`) stack
    26	(`dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json`)
    27	reports AC-013 at **p50 = 2048 ms, p99 = 2327 ms** on the
    28	N = 1,000,000 / dim 768 f32 fixture seeded by `VaryingEmbedder`
    29	(`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:296` and
    30	`:317`). AC-019 stress p99 = 8388 ms under bound 20964 ms; the
    31	bound is met today but the underlying per-query cost is the same
    32	hot path.
    33	
    34	The proposed budgets in
    35	`dev/adr/ADR-0.7.0-text-query-latency-gates-revised.md` are
    36	**80 ms p50 / 300 ms p99**. The measurement is therefore
    37	**~25–40× over** the budget envelope. The current
    38	`AC013_BUDGET_P50 = 50ms` / `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = 200ms` constants in
    39	`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` are
    40	the unindexed-path-pre-lock values; the revised budgets ADR drafts
    41	80 / 300 ms but they have not yet been pinned in the test, by
    42	design (the re-pin is itself the Pack 2 RED gate).
    43	
    44	**Root cause.** The hot SQL at
    45	`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`
    46	
    47	```
    48	SELECT rowid FROM vector_default
    49	WHERE embedding MATCH vec_f32(?1)
    50	ORDER BY distance
    51	LIMIT 10
    52	```
    53	
    54	drives a per-query O(N) brute-force scan over the
    55	`vector_default` vec0 table declared at
    56	`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3278-3283` as
    57	`USING vec0(embedding float[<dim>])` — i.e. a single global f32
    58	table with no metadata columns, no partition keys, no auxiliary
    59	index. At N = 1 M × dim 768 × 4 B that is 3.0 GB of memory
    60	streamed per query; the observed 2048 ms p50 corresponds to
    61	~1.5 GB/s, which sits at the single-thread memory-read ceiling
    62	on the canonical AMD EPYC 7763 runner. No SQLite engine knob can
    63	move this — the bytes-per-row × rows-per-query product is the
    64	floor. To close the gate we must either shrink the bytes per row,
    65	shrink the row count visited per query, or both.
    66	
    67	Cross-reference: `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md`
    68	§ "Problem restated" through § "Tier 1 combined estimate" enumerates
    69	the lever surface; the present ADR commits to the Tier-1 #4 +
    70	Tier-1 #1/#2 bundle as the load-bearing decision.
    71	
    72	## 2. Decision
    73	
    74	Adopt the following, to ship in two packs within the 0.7.0 release
    75	line (Pack 1 then Pack 2; pack boundary is for review granularity,
    76	not release-boundary):
    77	
    78	1. **Binary quantization** of the f32 embedding into a sibling
    79	   `bit[768]` column on the existing `vector_default` vec0 table
    80	   (Pack 1.1 default per
    81	   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md`
    82	   § 1.1). The bit column is computed via sqlite-vec's
    83	   `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and written inside the same
    84	   writer transaction as the existing f32 insert. Sibling-table
    85	   fallback (`vector_default_bin`) is selected only if the
    86	   sibling-column shape hits the vec0 metadata column limit
    87	   (16 cols). The f32 `embedding` column is **retained** for
    88	   the rerank phase and for the recall-floor ground-truth pass —
    89	   it has two jobs after Pack 1.
    90	
    91	2. **Two-phase query** (Pack 2): bit-KNN top-K=64 candidates →
    92	   f32 rerank → top-10. The exact SQL shape (subject to the
    93	   sqlite-vec syntax confirmation called out in
    94	   `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2)
    95	   replaces the single-phase scan at
    96	   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323`. K is
    97	   a named constant / config knob so future tuning is cheap; the
    98	   K = 64 default is taken from the Kyle Howells and Cohere
    99	   binary-quant benches cited in
   100	   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #4.
   101	
   102	3. **Schema extension shipped on the same migration** (Pack 1):
   103	   - `source_type TEXT` as a vec0 **partition_key**
   104	     (HITL-locked 2026-05-27 in
   105	     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`; cardinality ~6:
   106	     email, article, paper, meeting, note, todo). Maps from the
   107	     existing chunk-record vector kind at write time
   108	     (deterministic 1:1 mapping for the current single-kind
   109	     fixture; `source_type` is the authoritative going-forward
   110	     vocabulary).
   111	   - Additional metadata columns (`kind`, `created_at`, `tags`,
   112	     `project_mentions`, …) populated from the existing chunk
   113	     record. Per HITL Q5 in
   114	     `dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md` and
   115	     `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #1,
   116	     descriptive retrieval filters live in metadata columns +
   117	     WHERE predicates, not in partition keys. The vec0 limit is
   118	     16 metadata columns; the Pack 1 schema MUST budget headroom.
   119	
   120	4. **Recall floor: ≥ 0.90 recall@10** vs f32 brute-force ground
   121	   truth on the AC-013 fixture
   122	   (`dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md`,
   123	   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses #1).
   124	   Enforced by a new perf-gates test (`ac_NNN_recall_at_10`)
   125	   landed RED in Pack 2 before the query rewrite. Ground truth
   126	   is computed at test-setup via a one-pass brute-force scan
   127	   through the retained f32 column — single corpus, two jobs.
   128	
   129	5. **sqlite-vec pin stays `=0.1.7`**
   130	   (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml:18`). 0.1.7
   131	   already ships `bit[N]` and `vec_quantize_binary` per the
   132	   sqlite-vec release notes
   133	   (`dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` Tier 1 #4
   134	   citation). Bump to `=0.1.9` is allowed in Pack 1 **only if
   135	   needed** for constraint-column refinements; not required and
   136	   not recommended without justification.
   137	
   138	6. **Embedder unchanged.** The `EmbedderIdentity` contract,
   139	   `VaryingEmbedder`, and the profile-pinning logic at
   140	   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3248-3260` are
   141	   not touched. HITL Q2 in
   142	   `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § HITL responses
   143	   locked: KEEP existing embedder. Tier-1 #3 (smaller
   144	   embeddings) and Tier-1 #5 (matryoshka) are out of scope
   145	   for 0.7.0.
   146	
   147	7. **Single-writer + projection-cursor contracts preserved.**
   148	   Both column inserts commit in the same writer transaction at
   149	   the `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near
   150	   `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846`. The
   151	   writer-loop pins at `:2174` and `:2242` are not touched.
   152	   AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 behavior is preserved.
   153	
   154	## 3. Alternatives considered (and rejected)
   155	
   156	Each alternative below was considered against the AC-013 gap; the
   157	research doc carries the long-form analysis.
   158	
   159	- **Vectorlite (HNSW SQLite extension).** Mechanism: load a
   160	  separate `USING vectorlite(...)` virtual table backed by an
   161	  HNSW graph stored in shadow tables. Rejected because the
   162	  upstream has had no release since 2024-08-19, has no
   163	  published 1 M × 768 benchmark, and counts as a structural
   164	  architectural lever stacked on top of PCACHE2 — violates the
   165	  one-architectural-lever-per-release rule. Cited:
   166	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 2.
   167	
   168	- **sqlite-vec ANN alpha (v0.1.10-alpha.1).** Mechanism: use
   169	  the upstream-experimental ANN indices (`rescore`, `ivf`,
   170	  `DiskANN`). Rejected because the release is alpha-tagged and
   171	  upstream classifies it as not production-ready. Cited:
   172	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3,
   173	  sqlite-vec releases.
   174	
   175	- **Rust-side `usearch` / `instant-distance`.** Mechanism:
   176	  pull KNN out of SQLite into a Rust-side ANN library and
   177	  rebuild the search verb around it. Rejected because the
   178	  blast radius (leaving SQLite for the KNN step, snapshot /
   179	  freshness handshake redesign, AC-017 cursor-freshness
   180	  re-derivation) is far larger than two packs of in-place
   181	  schema + query work, and the data-encoding lever closes the
   182	  gap without it. Cited:
   183	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 3 (integration
   184	  shape C).
   185	
   186	- **Embedder swap (dim reduction 768 → 384 or 256).**
   187	  Mechanism: replace `VaryingEmbedder` with a smaller embedder
   188	  to shrink bytes-per-row. Rejected by HITL Q2 lock 2026-05-27:
   189	  keep existing embedder. Rationale: switching embedders
   190	  requires a profile rotation through
   191	  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles` and a corpus rebuild
   192	  (writer-cooperation cost), and even at dim 128 the
   193	  arithmetic-only saving is ~6× — well short of the ~25–40×
   194	  gap. Cited:
   195	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #3,
   196	  § HITL responses.
   197	
   198	- **Partitioning alone (metadata prefilter / partition_key
   199	  without quantization).** Mechanism: keep the f32 column,
   200	  add `source_type` partition_key + metadata columns, push
   201	  filters into the WHERE clause. Rejected as load-bearing:
   202	  the AC-013 fixture is single-kind, so partitioning yields
   203	  zero benefit at the gate. Partitioning is **kept** as a
   204	  bundled deliverable in Pack 1 because it is the correct
   205	  shape for real workloads and avoids a second migration in
   206	  0.7.1 — but it does not close the gate on its own. Cited:
   207	  `dev/notes/0.7.0-vector-cost-research.md` § Tier 1 #1, #2.
   208	
   209	## 4. Consequences
   210	
   211	- **Schema change (Pack 1).** `vector_default` gains the
   212	  `embedding_bin bit[768]` column, the `source_type` vec0
   213	  partition_key, and additional metadata columns (within the
   214	  vec0 16-column budget). Migration is a one-pass
   215	  `INSERT … SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM
   216	  vector_default` populating the bit column for the existing
   217	  corpus. Migration cost: ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the
   218	  1 M-row test corpus; ~64 s on the dev box per the handoff
   219	  estimate, well under the workflow timeout.
   220	
   221	- **Ingest cost (Pack 1).** The writer at the
   222	  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` insert site near
   223	  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2846` performs
   224	  a single additional `vec_quantize_binary()` and one extra
   225	  column write per row inside the same writer transaction.
   226	  No new commit; no new lock; no new SQLite handle. The
   227	  single-writer + projection-cursor freshness contract is
   228	  preserved bit-for-bit. Storage grows by ~3 % (96 B per row
   229	  on top of the 3072 B f32 footprint).
   230	
   231	- **Query-path rewrite (Pack 2).** Replace
   232	  `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2317-2323` with
   233	  the two-phase shape outlined in
   234	  `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md` § 2.2.
   235	  No change to the writer side, no change to the projection-
   236	  cursor handshake, no change to `register_sqlite_vec_extension`
   237	  at `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3107`. K = 64
   238	  is named as a constant for future tuning.
   239	
   240	- **Recall floor enforced as a RED test.** A new perf-gates
   241	  test (e.g. `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`) computes brute-force f32
   242	  ground truth at test-setup against the retained f32 column,
   243	  runs the production search path, and asserts
   244	  `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` on the AC-013 fixture. Lands RED in
   245	  Pack 2.1 alongside the latency budget re-pin
   246	  (`tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150` → 80 / 300 ms) and must
   247	  remain RED at canonical-CI N = 1 M scale until Pack 2.2's
   248	  query rewrite lands. Both gates GREEN at canonical-CI is
   249	  the Pack 2 close criterion.
   250	
   251	- **AC-019 carry.** The existing 10× bound on AC-019 stays
   252	  unchanged; the same two-phase query shape benefits AC-019
   253	  proportionally. AC-019 is expected to improve substantially
   254	  but no new bound is pinned here.
   255	
   256	- **AC-012 / AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020 unchanged.** The
   257	  writer-loop pins (`:2174`, `:2242`), the embedder profile
   258	  table, and the reader-pool concurrency surface are all
   259	  untouched. Pack 1 changes schema but not query semantics, so
