   324	---
   325	
   326	## Drafter's recommendation — locked plan
   327	
   328	**Tier 1 wins. Tiers 2 and 3 are not pursued in 0.7.0.**
   329	
   330	Ship in **two packs** within 0.7.0. Both packs live under the
   331	existing 0.7.0 release line; the split exists for review
   332	granularity, not for release-boundary reasons.
   333	
   334	### Pack 1 — schema migration + ingest double-write
   335	
   336	Lands the new schema and the new ingest path. No reader behavior
   337	change yet; queries still go through the existing f32 path.
   338	
   339	- **Add `bit[768]` column** (or sibling `vector_default_bin`
   340	  vec0 table) alongside the current f32 `embedding` column.
   341	  sqlite-vec 0.1.7 already supports `bit[N]` natively
   342	  ([release notes](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/releases))
   343	  — no upstream upgrade required.
   344	- **Add metadata columns + partition_key** to the vec0 schema
   345	  (Tier 1 #1 + #2). HITL-confirmed to ship in 0.7.0. Doesn't
   346	  help the AC-013 gate (single-kind fixture) but is the correct
   347	  shape for real workloads and avoids a second migration in
   348	  0.7.1. Partition_key candidate: vector kind from
   349	  `_fathomdb_vector_rows` (chunk-organised storage). Metadata
   350	  columns: at minimum a `kind` column; broader metadata schema
   351	  per the corpus / API work tracked separately.
   352	- **Ingest path change** in the writer (`lib.rs:2846` insert
   353	  site for `_fathomdb_vector_rows`): on every write, also
   354	  compute `vec_quantize_binary(embedding)` and insert into the
   355	  bit column. This is the "double-write" — both columns commit
   356	  in the same writer transaction, so the writer-lock and
   357	  projection-cursor freshness contract are unchanged.
   358	- **Schema migration** for existing data: rebuild the bit
   359	  column from the existing f32 corpus at upgrade time (one-pass
   360	  `INSERT ... SELECT vec_quantize_binary(embedding) FROM
   361	  vector_default`). Migration cost: ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write
   362	  for a 1 M row corpus; well under a minute on disk.
   363	- **Tests:** Pack 1 adds no new RED gate; existing AC-013
   364	  remains pinned at the unindexed 2048/2327 numbers until
   365	  Pack 2 lands. Pack 1's correctness gate is the migration
   366	  round-trip test (insert f32, read back bit column,
   367	  `vec_distance_hamming` matches the expected popcount).
   368	
   369	### Pack 2 — query-path swap + RED tests
   370	
   371	Switches the reader to the two-phase shape and pins the new
   372	budgets.
   373	
   374	- **`read_search_in_tx` query rewrite** at `lib.rs:2317-2323`:
   375	  two-phase query, bit-distance KNN top-K (K=64) → f32 rerank
   376	  for final top-10. K = 64 picked from binary-quant literature
   377	  (Kyle Howells, Cohere) to land recall@10 ≥ 95 % at ~50–100 ms;
   378	  may be tunable.
   379	- **AC-013 latency budget re-pin** in `tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`:
   380	  p50 ≤ 80 ms, p99 ≤ 300 ms (per ADR-0.7.0 draft). RED test
   381	  must fail at canonical-CI scale before Pack 2 code change.
